8.1. Extensions to the `CSSImportRule` interface[](#extensions-to-cssimportrule-interface)

The `CSSImportRule` interface is extended as follows:


```
partial interface [CSSImportRule](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssimportrule) {
 readonly attribute [CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring)? [layerName](#dom-cssimportrule-layername);
};

```


Its **`layerName`** attribute represents
 the [layer name](#layer-name) declared in the at-rule itself,
 and is an empty string if the layer is anonymous,
 or null if the at-rule does not declare a layer.

 8.2. The `CSSLayerBlockRule` interface[](#the-csslayerblockrule-interface)

The [CSSLayerBlockRule](#csslayerblockrule) interface represents
 the [@layer](#at-ruledef-layer) [block rule](#layer-block):


```
[[Exposed](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#Exposed)=Window]
interface CSSLayerBlockRule : [CSSGroupingRule](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssgroupingrule) {
 readonly attribute [CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring) [name](#dom-csslayerblockrule-name);
};

```


Its **`name`** attribute represents
 the [layer name](#layer-name) declared by the at-rule itself,
 and is an empty string if the layer is anonymous.

 
 [](#example-1c46cc0f) For example,
 additional nested context is not added from wrapping layer rules. 

```
@layer outer {
 @layer foo.bar { }
}

```


in this case the [name](#dom-csslayerblockrule-name) of the inner [@layer](#at-ruledef-layer) rule
 is “foo.bar” (and not “outer.foo.bar”).

 
 8.3. The `CSSLayerStatementRule` interface[](#the-csslayerstatementrule-interface)

The [CSSLayerStatementRule](#csslayerstatementrule) interface represents
 the [@layer](#at-ruledef-layer) [statement](#layer-empty):


```
[[Exposed](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#Exposed)=Window]
interface CSSLayerStatementRule : [CSSRule](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssrule) {
 readonly attribute [FrozenArray](https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-frozen-array)<[CSSOMString](https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-1/#cssomstring)> " href="#dom-csslayerstatementrule-namelist" id="ref-for-dom-csslayerstatementrule-namelist">nameList;
};

```


Its **`nameList`** attribute represents
 the list of [layer names](#layer-name) declared by the at-rule,
 normalized following the same rule as
 the [CSSLayerBlockRule](#csslayerblockrule)’s [name](#dom-csslayerblockrule-name) attribute.

